Class VertexShortestPathEuclidean

    • system.VertexImpl<java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,,java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,java.lang.Float>

  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Vertex<java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,,java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,java.lang.Float>, java.io.Serializable

    public final class VertexShortestPathEuclidean
extends VertexImpl<java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,,java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,java.lang.Float>
    The value associated with each vertex, v, is: 1. the minimum distance to vertex v 2. the vertexId of vertex u, where edge (u, v) is on a shortest path to v. Since these 2 items constitute a Message, vertexValue is a Message.

      • isSource

        public boolean isSource()
        Description copied from interface: Vertex
        The design intention is for this method to return true if and only if this vertex is a source: It has an in-edge degree of 0. However, jpregel does not check to see that no other vertex has this vertex as the endpoint of an out-edge. The application programmer has complete control over its implementation:
        Specified by:
        isSource in interface Vertex<java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,,java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,java.lang.Float>
        Specified by:
        isSource in class VertexImpl<java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,,java.awt.geom.Point2D.Float,java.lang.Float>
        Returns:
        true: The in-degree of this vertex == 0
        false: The in-degree of this vertex > 0.
